          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-ON NEUTRON CAPTURE CROSS SECTION MEASUREMENTS",
                " WITH THE ACTIVATION TECHNIQUE IN THE MEV",
                " REGION.-"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "2SWDLND"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 3 MV TANDEM VAN DE GRAAFF."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " PROTON-TRITIUM REACTION AND"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " DEUTERON-TRITIUM REACTION.",
                " THE PROTONS AND THE DEUTERONS WERE ACCELERATED",
                " BY THE VAN DE GRAAFF MACHINE.",
                " SEVERAL TARGETS WERE USED AND INVESTIGATED WITH",
                " RESPECT TO THE PRIMARY NEUTRON BACKGROUND.",
                " - THIN TITANIUM LAYERS, ABOUT 2 MG/CM**2",
                "   THICKNESS IN WHICH THE DEUTERIUM OR TRITIUM",
                "   WAS ABSORBED, EAVAPORATED ONTO A 0.5 MM",
                "   THICK BACKING. IT WAS SHOWN THAT THE TI(T)",
                "   CANNOT BE USED ANYMORE BEYOND 4.5 MEV",
                "   NEUTRON ENERGY, AND THAT DEUTERIUM TARGETS",
                "   ARE PREFERABLE ABOVE 3.0 MEV. THE ENERGY",
                "   RANGE CAN THAN BE EXTENDED BY 1. MEV.",
                " - DEUTERIUM GAS TARGET WITH A 4.2 MG/CM**2",
                "   THICK MO-FOIL AS ENTRANCE WINDOW AND GOLD",
                "   AS A BEAM STOP. THIS WAY THE NEUTRON ENERGY",
                "   RANGE CAN BE EXTENDED BY SEVERAL MEV.",
                " - ALSO A T(ZR-90) TARGET WITH NATURAL ZR",
                "   HAS BEEN TESTED."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".PLACED AT DISTANCES SUCH THAT THE SOLID ANGLE",
                " SUBTENDED BY THE SAMPLES AT THE TARGET WAS THE",
                " SAME IN ALL CASES. FOR THE STUDIES OF THE",
                " THICKNESS DEPENDENCE OF THE ACTIVATION YIELDS,",
                " INDIUM SAMPLES WERE USED WITH A DIAMETER OF 10.",
                " MM AND A THICKNESS RANGING FROM 0.18 TO 1.66",
                " GRAMS/CM**2. THE TARGET-SAMPLE DISTANCE DEPENDENCE",
                " WAS DETERMINED USING 0.6 GRAMS/CM**2 SAMPLES WITH",
                " DIAMETERS RANGING FROM 5.0 TO 20. MM."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".ACTIVATION.",
                ".DEPENDENCE OF THE ACTIVATION YIELDS ON SAMPLE",
                " THICKNESS AND EFFECTIVE TARGET-SAMPLE DISTANCE",
                " HAS BEEN INVESTIGATED TO ALLOW DETAILED",
                " CORRECTIONS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LONGC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " TO MONITOR THE NEUTRON FLUX. AT 1.2 M",
                " FROM THE TARGET."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
