          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".PRIMARY NEUTRON BACKGROUND, I.E. NEUTRONS",
                " PRODUCED BY (P,N) AND (D,N) REACTIONS IN THE",
                " TARGET BACKING AND ABSORPTION MATERIALS AND",
                " IN THE APERTURES ALONG THE BEAM LINE. THIS WAS",
                " DONE BY USING TARGETS WITH NATURAL HYDROGEN",
                " IN STEAD OF D OR T. (EMPTY TARGETS).",
                ".SECONDARY NEUTRON BACKGROUND. IT CONSISTS OF",
                " SEVERAL CONTRIBUTIONS ,",
                " - NEUTRONS PRODUCED BY INELASTIC SCATTERING",
                "   IN THE SAMPLE. THIS WAS CORRECTED FOR BY",
                "   STUDYING THE ACTIVATION YIELD AS A FUNCTION",
                "   OF THE SAMPLE THICKNESS.",
                " - NEUTRONS PRODUCED BY INELASTIC SCATTERING",
                "   IN STRUCTURAL MATERIALS NEAR THE TARGET-",
                "   SAMPLE ASSEMBLY AND NEUTRONS SCATTERED BY",
                "   THE WALLS OF THE ROOM. THIS WAS CORRECTED",
                "   FOR BY THE STUDYING THE ACTIVATION YIELD",
                "   AS A FUNCTION OF THE TARGET-SAMPLE DISTANCE.",
                " BOTH EFFECTS PRODUCE NEUTRONS WITH LOWER",
                " ENERGIES WITH HIGHER (N,G) CROSS SECTIONS",
                " AND ARE THUS IMPORTANT."
              ]
            }
          ],
